  "text": "Activating transcription factor 3 is a commonly used surrogate marker for neuronal damage after peripheral nerve injury. [CITATION_1] In this study, ATF3 was increased in the ipsilateral lumbar DRG at both 3 and 14 days after CCI (P , 0.001). However, ATF3 expression was attenuated at both time points by 6 weeks of voluntary wheel running ceasing before CCI (P , 0.05; Fig. 3C ).",
